title: Will Star Wars force holiday Oscar films to the curb
text:
Will 'Star Wars' force holiday, Oscar films to the curb? 
Fox News Friday 23rd October, 2015 
LOS ANGELES â€“ Almost every theater in America will have multiple screens devoted to 'Star Wars: The Force Awakens' when it opens nationwide on December 17. This is the first time a "Star Wars" movie has been released over the holiday season, with all six previous "Star Wars" films having been released over Memorial Day weekend, the traditional release date for summer blockbusters. 
The move to the week before Christmas has at least one A-lister with a competing movie a little nervous.
